This paper deals with network security and machine learning, which are both relevant to the categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) and "Networking and Internet Architecture" (cs.NI). The use of predictive models and feature extraction also suggests a connection to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). Finally, the experimental research strategy and focus on performance evaluation could also be relevant to "Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
